An all-German final looks on the cards in the Europa League if Eintracht Frankfurt can hold off West Ham at home and RB Leipzig avoid defeat in Scotland. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Salernitana vs Venezia: Salernitana and Venezia are both in the relegation zone in Serie A but have this catch-up game to offer them the chance of still saving their top-flight status. Salernitana have won the last four meetings between the pair.M2 Djurgarden vs Helsingborg: Djurgarden’s home record against Helsingborg is 13 wins, five draws and four defeats in 22 past visits.M3 Eintracht Frankfurt vs West Ham United: Bidding to reach a first European final in 42 years, Eintracht Frankfurt are in control of their Europa League semi-final against West Ham thanks to a 2-1 first-leg win in London that maintained their unbeaten record in Europe this season, although the English side can take heart from a resounding second-leg away win in the quarter-finals.M4 Olympique Marseille vs Feyenoord Rotterdam: Marseille need to make it four home wins out of four in the UEFA Europa Conference League if they are to reach the inaugural final at the expense of a Feyenoord side who ended the French club’s perfect record in the competition with a 3-2 win in the semi-final first leg in Rotterdam.M5 Glasgow Rangers vs RB Leipzig: Rangers will hope for an encore of a memorable quarter-final comeback as they return to Ibrox for the second leg of their UEFA Europa League semi-final against a Leipzig side looking to protect a 1-0 advantage from the first leg in Germany and reach a European final for the first time.M6 Roma vs Leicester City: Roma and Leicester meet in the Italian capital for the decisive second leg of their Europa Conference League semi-final with everything to play for after the English side, seeking to reach a European final for the first time, came from behind to draw their home leg 1-1.M7 Fortaleza vs River Plate: Fortaleza are competing in their first Copa Libertadores campaign but lost two of their opening three group games. River Plate registered a 7-0 away win in the Argentine league on Sunday.M8 Everton vs Sao Paulo: Sao Paulo have won all three group games in the Copa Sudamericana, including 2-0 at home to the Chileans last month. Everton are second in Group D with four points.M9 RB Bragantino vs Velez Sarsfield: Copa Libertadores rookies Bragantino have four points from their first three group games while Velez Sarsfield have a single point from when they drew 2-2 at home against the Brazilians.M10 Universidad Catolica vs Santos: Both clubs have four points at the halfway stage of their Copa Sudamericana Group C campaign, one point behind leaders Union La Calera. Suggested permutation:R16.00 1 x 1 x 2,3 x 1 x 2,3 x 1,2 x 1 x 3 x 1 x 3